.TH DBX-LIST 1 "2026-06-20" "dbx 0.35.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-list \- list available backups
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx list
.RI [ host ]
.RI [ database ]
.PP
.B dbx ls
.RI [ host ]
.RI [ database ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
List backup files under
.I $DATA_DIR
(default
.IR ~/.data/dbx ),
showing filename, size, and modification time.
.PP
With no arguments, lists every host with backups. With just
.IR host ,
lists every database. With both, lists individual backup files
newest-first.
.SH EXAMPLES
Show every database with backups for host
.IR production :
.PP
.RS
.nf
dbx list production
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show every backup for
.IR production/myapp ,
newest first:
.PP
.RS
.nf
dbx list production myapp
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DBX_DATA_DIR
Override the default backup-data directory.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.data/dbx/<host>/<database>/<file>.sql.zst[.age|.gpg]
The backup files
.B list
walks.
.TP
.I ~/.data/dbx/<host>/<database>/<file>.meta.json
Sidecar metadata read for the size / flavor columns.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-restore (1),
.BR dbx-verify (1),
.BR dbx-clean (1).
